# Use shadcn Components Over Bare HTML

Always prefer shadcn/ui components over native HTML elements for consistent styling and UX.

## Standard

- ❌ **Avoid**: `<select>`, `<button>`, `<input>`, `<textarea>` with manual styling
- ✅ **Use**: shadcn Select, Button, Input, Textarea components

## Exceptions

Native HTML is acceptable for:
- Semantic structure (`<form>`, `<label>`, `<div>`, `<span>`, `<section>`, etc.)
- Components not available in shadcn/ui
- Custom components that wrap shadcn primitives

## Implementation

For implementation patterns and migration guide, see the `ui-components` skill.
